// Rights groups welcomed the passage of the bill, which had stirred opposition from not only Republican lawmakers but also the powerful US Chamber of Commerce.<br />
&ldquo;The bill illustrates that effectively combating Uygur forced labour will inevitably require genuine engagement from American companies,&rdquo; said Omer Kanat, executive director of the Washington-based Uyghur Human Rights Project. &ldquo;If the companies themselves refuse to act, it&rsquo;s up to our government to compel them to do so.&rdquo;//
